This paper deals with querying graph-structured data, which is a common topic in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for finding a path of minimum length, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper involves formal language theory and context-free grammars, which are also relevant to theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the practical value of the proposed query semantics, which could be of interest to machine learning researchers (cs.LG) working with graph data.
